                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450407-951-offence-1 t18450407-cd-75"></join>26th of Feb</rs>., at <placeName id="t18450407-geo-15">
                        <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450407-951-offence-1 t18450407-geo-15"></join>St. Mary, Islington</placeName>, and stealing therein, 1 printed book, value 17<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 trinket-case, 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.; 4 cigar-cases, 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 1 sraoking-pipe, 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; his pro<lb></lb>perty.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-926" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-926" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-926" type="surname" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-926" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES MARTIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in a cottage in Albion-gardens, Maiden-lane, in the parish of St. Mary, Islington. On the 26th of Feb. I left home about half-past five o'clock—the door which is in two halves was fastened and bolted, and the windows safe—they do not open—I returned at ten at night, found the top part of the door broken open, the bolt wrenched completely off, and only hanging by part of the screws—I missed a book, a trinket case, a cigar case, brass tube and pipe, which were safe when I went out—I have seen nothing but the book since—this now produced is it—it is the "Builder", and is my own binding.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-927" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-927" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-927" type="surname" value="WILSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-927" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WILSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Mr. Gill, a pawnbroker, in Wilmot-street, Brunswick-square. On the morning of the 27th of Feb. the prisoner pledged this book—I knew him before, and am sure he is the person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-928" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-928" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
